cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the class of visibly pushdown languages and their properties in the sliding window model. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the space complexity of sliding window algorithms for these languages. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as visibly pushdown languages are a subclass of context-free languages, which are studied in logic and automata theory. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) may be relevant as the paper deals with the compression of strings in the sliding window model. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) may be relevant as the paper discusses the properties of languages and their recognition by algorithms.
